                "content": "What matters most to me: Quality over price",
                "importance": 8,
                "emotional_valence": 0.0,
                "source_stimulus_id": null,
                "last_accessed": "2026-04-04T05:15:56.407992Z"
              },
              {
                "id": "feeeef88-cf0c-4ad6-bd13-1edcbfd4f55e",
                "timestamp": "2026-04-04T05:15:56.408022Z",
                "type": "observation",
                "content": "Something I always navigate: You tend to be medium price-sensitive \u2014 you balance affordability with value, willing to pay more for quality but keeping an eye on the total spend.",
                "importance": 8,
                "emotional_valence": 0.0,
                "source_stimulus_id": null,
                "last_accessed": "2026-04-04T05:15:56.408022Z"
              },
              {
                "id": "1a04a53b-feb3-4ed5-923a-6b3a3d6bbc00",
                "timestamp": "2026-04-04T05:15:56.408034Z",
                "type": "observation",
                "content": "A defining moment in my life: During her postgraduate program at a Mumbai university, she received a partial merit scholarship but still had to manage a tight monthly stipend of \u20b98,000, meticulously tracking every rupee in a spreadsheet she built herself. \u2014 That experience hardwired her to anchor every major purchase decision on price first, and to trust her own calculations over anyone else's recommendations \u2014 habits that persist even now with a stable dual income.",
                "importance": 8,
                "emotional_valence": 0.0,
                "source_stimulus_id": null,
                "last_accessed": "2026-04-04T05:15:56.408034Z"
              },
              {
                "id": "a2009085-d9f8-4901-8ee6-44722e2e85ca",
                "timestamp": "2026-04-04T05:15:56.408046Z",
                "type": "observation",
                "content": "A defining moment in my life: After her daughter was born, she and her husband identified a larger 3BHK flat in Powai they desperately wanted, but the EMI projections left too thin a safety margin, so she built a 24-month savings plan and chose to wait instead of stretching. \u2014 The experience crystallized her moderate risk tolerance \u2014 she learned she could hold aspiration without acting on it impulsively, but also felt the quiet ache of deferral that now underlies her ongoing tension between wanting more and spending carefully.",
                "importance": 8,
                "emotional_valence": 0.0,
                "source_stimulus_id": null,
                "last_accessed": "2026-04-04T05:15:56.408046Z"
              },
              {
                "id": "8d94f675-c045-4f70-b138-0ed7d0e8d1b8",
                "timestamp": "2026-04-04T05:15:56.408056Z",
                "type": "observation",
                "content": "A defining moment in my life: A routine blood test during her pregnancy flagged borderline glucose levels, sending her into weeks of anxious research into gestational diabetes and elimination diets including a brief flirtation with low-carb eating. \u2014 Follow-up tests confirmed everything normalized, leaving her with residual health-consciousness but no lasting dietary restriction \u2014 explaining why her diabetic concern and keto adherence both remain near-negligible today.",
                "importance": 8,
                "emotional_valence": 0.0,
                "source_stimulus_id": null,
                "last_accessed": "2026-04-04T05:15:56.408056Z"
              }
            ],
