            "event": "During her postgraduate program at Delhi University, she discovered a calculation error in her fellowship disbursement that the department had overlooked for two semesters \u2014 she caught it herself after building a spreadsheet to track every rupee.",
            "lasting_impact": "This confirmed her instinct to verify everything personally rather than trust institutions, cementing her self-reliant trust orientation and analytical approach to all financial decisions."
          },
          {
            "title": "The Flat That Almost Broke Them",
            "when": "age 31",
            "event": "She and her husband stretched to buy a 3BHK in Dwarka on an EMI that consumed 52% of their combined income for the first 18 months, forcing her to track grocery costs by unit price and abandon a planned family vacation to Shimla.",
            "lasting_impact": "The experience branded price as her primary decision filter and created a persistent tension between the lifestyle she envisions and the budget discipline she knows is necessary."
          },
          {
            "title": "The Rejected Promotion Cycle",
            "when": "age 35",
            "event": "After being passed over for a senior manager role that went to a less-qualified external hire, she enrolled in a part-time data analytics certification while still managing her full workload and two school-aged children.",
            "lasting_impact": "The episode reinforced her moderate risk tolerance \u2014 she responds to setbacks with structured self-improvement rather than bold pivots \u2014 and kept her focus on steady establishing-phase goals over speculative leaps."
          }
