          {
            "title": "The EMI Miscalculation",
            "when": "age 27",
            "event": "After landing his first salaried job in Hyderabad, he financed a mid-range laptop and a two-wheeler simultaneously, underestimating how the combined EMIs would strain his monthly budget for nearly 18 months.",
            "lasting_impact": "This experience hardened his instinct to run detailed cost calculations before any purchase, cementing price as his primary decision filter and making him deeply skeptical of aspirational spending that outpaces income."
          },
          {
            "title": "The Postgraduate Thesis Defense",
            "when": "age 24",
            "event": "During his master's thesis defense in data analytics, his methodology was challenged by the panel and he successfully defended every assumption using his own documented research, without relying on his advisor's backing.",
            "lasting_impact": "The experience validated his habit of trusting his own analysis over external authority, which now manifests as a strong self-reliant trust orientation when evaluating products, advice, or financial decisions."
          },
          {
            "title": "The Apartment Shortlist Spreadsheet",
            "when": "age 30",
            "event": "When searching for a flat in Hyderabad after his son was born, he built a 40-row comparison spreadsheet covering rent, commute cost, maintenance charges, and school proximity before signing a lease in Kondapur.",
            "lasting_impact": "The process reinforced his analytical-conscientious personality as a practical survival tool in a high-stakes environment, and the moderate outcome \u2014 a decent but not aspirational flat \u2014 quietly normalized the tension between what he wants and what he can responsibly afford."
          }
