            "title": "The Budget Spreadsheet That Saved the Flat",
            "when": "age 26",
            "event": "When Priya and her husband moved into their first rented flat in Pune after marriage, they nearly ran out of savings by month three due to unplanned furniture and deposit costs; she built a detailed monthly tracking spreadsheet that mapped every rupee.",
            "lasting_impact": "This crisis hardwired her into a price-first decision-making mode and a deep distrust of advice from anyone other than her own data \u2014 she trusts her spreadsheet more than any salesperson or friend's recommendation."
