          {
            "title": "The Budget Spreadsheet That Changed Everything",
            "when": "age 22",
            "event": "During his first month in Bengaluru after relocating for his postgraduate program, Arjun miscalculated his rent and groceries and overdrew his account by \u20b94,200, forcing him to borrow from a classmate he barely knew.",
            "lasting_impact": "He built a meticulous monthly expense tracker that he still updates every Sunday, cementing his primary value driver around price and his instinct to trust his own calculations over anyone else's advice."
          },
          {
            "title": "The Startup Offer He Almost Took",
            "when": "age 24",
            "event": "A well-funded Series A startup offered Arjun a role with a 30% salary bump but entirely in ESOPs with a 4-year cliff, and after two weeks of modelling scenarios on a spreadsheet, he declined in favor of a stable full-time position at a mid-size firm.",
            "lasting_impact": "The deliberation left him with a calibrated but uncomfortable awareness of his own risk tolerance \u2014 he wants upside but cannot yet absorb downside, feeding a persistent tension between who he is now and who he intends to become."
          },
          {
            "title": "Eating Alone at the Mess Counter",
            "when": "age 23",
            "event": "For nearly six months during his postgraduate thesis crunch, Arjun ate every meal at the hostel mess by himself, skipping social dinners to save both money and time, finding he neither missed the company as much as expected nor felt entirely comfortable with that realization.",
            "lasting_impact": "He settled into a moderate social rhythm \u2014 present enough not to feel isolated, withdrawn enough to protect his schedule and budget \u2014 which now defines his balanced but unremarkable social orientation."
          }
        ],
