    {
      "enrichment_applied": true,
      "enrichment_provider": "sarvam",
      "enrichment_scope": "narrative_and_examples",
      "persona_id": "pg-pg-011",
      "enriched_narrative": {
        "first_person": "I run every number myself before I commit to anything. That's not paranoia \u2014 that's earned wisdom. Back when the financial crisis hit our household, I was the one who built the spreadsheet that kept us afloat while everyone else was taking advice from people with commissions to earn. Nobody was watching out for us except me.\n\nNow I'm in a better place \u2014 upper-middle income, two kids in school, Hyderabad's costs climbing every year \u2014 but the instinct never left. I want more for my family than where we currently stand, and I know exactly what's standing between us and that: every rupee I don't optimize.\n\nI'll cross-reference MoneyControl and ET analyses, verify the data myself anyway. Price isn't cheapness. Price is control. And control is the one thing I refuse to outsource to anyone.",
        "third_person": "Aakash Gupta is a 42-year-old Hyderabad-based IT professional navigating the careful arithmetic of upper-middle-class ambition within real financial boundaries. His undergraduate degree and full-time employment have shaped a pragmatic worldview, but the defining force behind his decision-making is a past financial crisis that compelled him to personally rescue his nuclear family through disciplined budgeting \u2014 the kind of crisis that turns a man into his own CFO.\n\nThat experience hardwired structural distrust of external advisors and converted self-reliance into identity. This explains why, despite moderate analytical confidence, Aakash invests considerable time studying expert sources \u2014 MoneyControl reports, ET research, RBI guidance \u2014 not to outsource judgment, but to arm himself before making independent calls. Price functions as his non-negotiable floor in Hyderabad's competitive market, yet he remains willing to stretch for demonstrable quality. The persistent tension in his profile \u2014 aspiring beyond his current constraints \u2014 drives his deliberate, verification-heavy switching behavior."
      },
      "cultural_references_added": [
        "MoneyControl (credentialed financial analysis source)",
        "ET (Economic Times, official business publication)",
        "RBI (Reserve Bank of India, official monetary authority)",
        "rupee (currency-specific terminology)",
        "Hyderabad's market context"
      ],
      "contextual_examples_replaced": [
